  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dbb\u0dda\u0d9c\u0dd4 \u0d8b\u0d9a\u0dd4\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dc3\u0ddd \u0dc4\u0dc3\u0dd4\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0d9c\u0dad\u0dca \u0dbb\u0db1\u0dca \u0da2\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0db8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Gold smuggling caught by customs hawks",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A Sri Lankan airline passenger who tried to illegally bring a stock of gold worth 142 million rupees to Sri Lanka, which had been prepared using sophisticated methods at the foreign factory to mislead the customs officials, was arrested by a group of officers of the Customs Narcotics Control Division at the arrival terminal of Katunayake Airport this morning. Has been arrested.",
        "He is a 25-year-old young man who resides in Dehiwala area of \u200b\u200bColombo and works as a financial consultant in a private business firm.",
        "He had arrived at Katunayake Airport at 09.05 in the morning from Bahrain on Gulf Airlines flight GF-144.",
        "Based on the suspicions of the customs officials about this passenger, he was arrested and checked. There, gold plates were hidden in the lid of 06 Suwada Vilawun bottles that he was bringing. In addition to this, in the lids of 12 Tiger Balm packs, as well as 06 carbon pens, gold rods were inserted into the carbon ink tube. There, these pens were being written well, and these discoveries were made during the scan checks conducted by the customs officials.",
        "In addition to this, a key that he brought was also made entirely of gold, and the buckle of the waist belt that he was carrying was also made of gold.",
        "In addition, gold bars were placed in the frames of two saucepans he had brought. All these were meticulously finished in the manufacturing factories in order to mislead the customs officials.",
        "These goods contained gold weighing 682 grams and their value is one crore forty two lakh rupees. The Katunayake airport customs officials have currently detained this young man and are conducting further investigations on this matter."
      ],
